data.title: EMCC hires former Boaz, UNA star Milwee

data.text:
SCOOBA, Miss. — East Mississippi Community College announced Thursday that A.J. Milwee, a former standout quarterback at Boaz High School and the University of North Alabama, was hired as an assistant football coach for the Lions.

Milwee will work with the EMCC quarterbacks after having served as a graduate assistant coach at North Alabama under head coach Terry Bowden.

Milwee was a two-time Alabama Sports Writers Association All-State selection at Boaz and was named The Gadsden Times’ Player of the Year in 2003.

Milwee spent one season under Mike Shula at Alabama as a walk-on before transferring to UNA. While at UNA, Milwee set all-time school records for most career passing yards (8,436), pass completions (677), passing attempts (1,030), touchdown passes (73), total offense (9,401) and touchdowns responsible for (91). He compiled a 33-5 record while at UNA.
